The '''Turkish Derivatives Exchange''' (: ''Vadeli İşlem ve Opsiyon Borsası''), commonly known by its acronym, '''TurkDex''', is a Turkish  , trading contracts based on currencies, indexes, bonds, interest rates, and commodities. Trading at the exchange commenced on 4 February 2005. The monthly volume on all contracts is around 3.5 million.
As of August 2006 the exchange had 59 members.